Type: Package
Package: trendfiltering
Title: The state-of-the-art method for denoising 1D signals
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Collin A.",
             family = "Politsch",
             role = c("aut","cre"),
             email = "collinpolitsch@gmail.com",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3727-9167")))
Description: A suite of tools for denoising one-dimensional signals
  with trend filtering. Optimizing the hyparameter via Stein's
  unbiased risk estimate or V-fold cross validation with an
  arbitrary validation loss functional. One-standard-error
  rules, relaxed trend filtering, and bootstrap variations for
  uncertainty quantification in every data analysis setting.
License: MIT
URL: https://capolitsch.github.io/trendfiltering
BugReports: https://github.com/capolitsch/trendfiltering/issues
